is like understanding a cat; neither ever says anything back and you can't keep a conversation with them. All art is like this, but not only art is like this; nature, the past, numbers are also like this." Tamen takes up many central issues in aesthetics and the philosophy of art, including the connection between art and having fuzzy ideas about art, the mistake of imagining that art-decisions are put forth by art-courts where you are both judge and jury, and the notion that what happens with art also happens to you.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jul 2019) 0aAlice (Fictitious character : Carroll) 0aArtxPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Aesthetics.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE PHILOSOPHY  2012z978311029405708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET PHILOSOPHIE  2012z9783110294040oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP Complete eBook Package 2011-2014z978311037488908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package 2012z978311037491908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044220508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2014z978311045951708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHUP eBook Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066256640uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/harvard.9780674067950423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780674067950.jpg  a978-3-11-029405-7  E-BOOK PACKAGE PHILOSOPHY  2012b2012  a978-3-11-037488-9  HUP Complete eBook Package 2011-2014  a978-3-11-037491-9  HUP eBook Package 2012b2012  a978-3-11-044220-5  HUP eBook Package Backlist 2005-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-045951-7